  <section class="not-prose mt-12 rounded-lg border border-buff-border bg-buff-darker p-6">
    <h2 class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold text-white">Sports Streaming Glossary</h2>
    <p class="mb-6 text-sm text-buff-muted">Common terms and concepts related to live sports streaming on Buffstreams and other platforms.</p>
    <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-buff-border bg-buff-card p-4">
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-bold text-white">HD Streaming</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-buff-muted">High-definition video streaming at 720p or 1080p resolution. HD streams on Buffstreams provide clearer picture quality than standard definition with better detail during fast-paced sports action.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-buff-border bg-buff-card p-4">
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-bold text-white">Bitrate</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-buff-muted">The amount of data transmitted per second in a video stream. Higher bitrates produce better image quality. Buffstreams HD streams typically use 1500-4000 kbps bitrates depending on resolution and source.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-buff-border bg-buff-card p-4">
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-bold text-white">Stream Latency</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-buff-muted">The delay between live action and when it appears on screen. Buffstreams streams typically have 15-45 seconds of latency which is standard for web-based streaming and allows for buffer management.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-buff-border bg-buff-card p-4">
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-bold text-white">CDN</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-buff-muted">Content Delivery Network that distributes video streams across multiple geographic servers. CDNs reduce buffering by serving video from the server closest to the viewer's location.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-buff-border bg-buff-card p-4">
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-bold text-white">Adaptive Bitrate</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-buff-muted">Technology that automatically adjusts video quality based on available internet bandwidth. When network conditions change, the stream quality scales up or down without manual intervention to prevent buffering.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-buff-border bg-buff-card p-4">
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-bold text-white">Buffer</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-buff-muted">A temporary data storage area that pre-loads video content before playback. Buffering smooths out network fluctuations but can cause playback delays if the buffer empties faster than it refills due to bandwidth constraints.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

